<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n03067a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n03" href="#n03067a">N03 (VI.B.3)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n03all.htm#n03067a"> 67(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> reproach by self / accusation</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[Letter from RW to MW, Zurich, 17 March 1853]</font> &ldquo;LADY, &mdash; God henceforth will protect you from my rude manners &hellip; If, in future, I impose upon myself more frequent acts of self-denial &hellip; rest assured that this is because I am determined, above all else, to obtain forgiveness &hellip;&rdquo; &hellip; Here may be seen a characteristic peculiar to Wagner, that subtle art of <mark>reproaching through self-accusation</mark> <small> Edouard Schur&eacute;, <a name="ESWI" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#ESWI"><cite title="source">Woman: the Inspirer</cite></a>, trans. by Fred Rothwell (1918) 9-10</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
